Constructor types that return the all type or the unknown type currently fail to parse:

/** @type {function(new:?)} */ var foo = function() {};
/** @type {function(new:*)} */ var bar = function() {};

foo.js:1: ERROR - Bad type annotation. type not recognized due to syntax error
/** @type {function(new:?)} */ var foo = function() {};
                        ^

foo.js:2: ERROR - Bad type annotation. type not recognized due to syntax error
/** @type {function(new:*)} */ var bar = function() {};
                        ^

This is an issue for a code generator that I'm working on.

The parse simply needs to change from only accepting a type name to accepting a type (a one line change + tests, I would think).  It seems reasonable that this could be a record type or anything else.   

The work around it to use a typedef:

/** @typedef {?} */
var Unknown;

/** @type {function(new:Unknown)} */
